threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a backdoor/Remote Access Trojan (RAT). It establishes C2 communication using WinHTTP APIs, attempting to connect through various proxy configurations, including by parsing Firefox profiles (`profiles.ini`, `prefs.js`) and IE's registry settings. It implements a remote shell by executing commands via `cmd.exe /c` and capturing the output. It also has a custom `rundll` command to load and execute functions from arbitrary DLLs. A key IOC is the C2 URI pattern `/%x/archive/%02d%02d%02d%02d.html`, which is constructed using the victim's ID and current time.
